metadata.name: Damn everything but the circus! #49
metadata.description:

metadata.name: Unsolicited abstraction of modern times #168
metadata.description:
This piece is an abstraction and a reflection on the last era, on all that we have built and become. Are we proud of it or has it just been the result of iterating through the days? Since the technology boom, we have experienced great improvements, but perhaps also massive ...mistakes?‚Ä®‚Ä®

Inspired by textbooks of the 80s, with elements that remind us of industry, technology, networks and systems, "Unsolicited abstraction of modern times" invites us to question our work to date. Has everything really changed?

unknowable 2022




Usage:
press [s] - save pixels (png)
press [p] - save vectors (svg)

metadata.name: Extreme Ways Sketchup #197
metadata.description:
¬´¬†Extreme ways are back again..."

This artwork is proposed as a gift for all Extreme Ways owners (at mint time of Extreme Ways Sketchup).
Very few changes in the code with respect to Extreme Ways (mainly freezing or imposing strict limits to main parameters).

It can be viewed as a sketchup of the first steps of Extreme Ways.

Will you keep it ?
Will you sell it (and then earn 25% of royalties) ?
Will you try to get one that looks like your Extreme Ways to get a match ?
It's up to you...

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key ‚Äôs‚Äô  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution


For Extreme Ways, a guide for interactivity is available : 
https://sites.google.com/view/tidally-disrupted-star/extreme-ways/interactivity

metadata.name: Desert Solitude #60
metadata.description: "Desert Solitude" is an exploration of my love for crystals, architecture, being one with nature, escaping technology and becoming ok with the idea of being alone. The series was derived using diffusion Ai models and put together in a generative image composition on fx(hash) May 2022. 123 editions were made available.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #355
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Penumbra #3
metadata.description:
Penumbra is a geometric exploration of the possible outcomes from 3 basic rules:

1) Place some walls
2) Place some light sources
3) Draw the resulting shadows

This series is a small thank you to the collectors of Umbra :)
